6950

    
    

    

    


    

    
6951

    
    

    
static bool IsRootOfOpenMenuSet()

    


    

    
6952

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
6953

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
6954

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
6955

    
    

    
    if ((g.OpenPopupStack.Size <= g.BeginPopupStack.Size) || (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu))

    


    

    
6956

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
6957

    
    

    

    


    

    
6958

    
    

    
    // Initially we used 'upper_popup->OpenParentId == window->IDStack.back()' to differentiate multiple menu sets from each others

    


    

    
6959

    
    

    
    // (e.g. inside menu bar vs loose menu items) based on parent ID.

    


    

    
6960

    
    

    
    // This would however prevent the use of e.g. PuhsID() user code submitting menus.

    


    

    
6961

    
    

    
    // Previously this worked between popup and a first child menu because the first child menu always had the _ChildWindow flag,

    


    

    
6962

    
    

    
    // making  hovering on parent popup possible while first child menu was focused - but this was generally a bug with other side effects.

    


    

    
6963

    
    

    
    // Instead we don't treat Popup specifically (in order to consistently support menu features in them), maybe the first child menu of a Popup

    


    

    
6964

    
    

    
    // doesn't have the _ChildWindow flag, and we rely on this IsRootOfOpenMenuSet() check to allow hovering between root window/popup and first child menu.

    


    

    
6965

    
    

    
    // In the end, lack of ID check made it so we could no longer differentiate between separate menu sets. To compensate for that, we at least check parent window nav layer.

    


    

    
6966

    
    

    
    // This fixes the most common case of menu opening on hover when moving between window content and menu bar. Multiple different menu sets in same nav layer would still

    


    

    
6967

    
    

    
    // open on hover, but that should be a lesser problem, because if such menus are close in proximity in window content then it won't feel weird and if they are far apart

    


    

    
6968

    
    

    
    // it likely won't be a problem anyone runs into.

    


    

    
6969

    
    

    
    const ImGuiPopupData* upper_popup = &g.OpenPopupStack[g.BeginPopupStack.Size];

    


    

    
6970

    
    

    
    return (window->DC.NavLayerCurrent == upper_popup->ParentNavLayer && upper_popup->Window && (upper_popup->Window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu));

    


    

    
6971

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
6972

    
    

    

    


    

    
6973

    
    

    
bool ImGui::BeginMenuEx(const char* label, const char* icon, bool enabled)

    


    

    
6974

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
6975

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();

    


    

    
6976

    
    

    
    if (window->SkipItems)

    


    

    
6977

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
6978

    
    

    

    


    

    
6979

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
6980

    
    

    
    const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;

    


    

    
6981

    
    

    
    const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);

    


    

    
6982

    
    

    
    bool menu_is_open = IsPopupOpen(id, ImGuiPopupFlags_None);

    


    

    
6983

    
    

    

    


    

    
6984

    
    

    
    // Sub-menus are ChildWindow so that mouse can be hovering across them (otherwise top-most popup menu would steal focus and not allow hovering on parent menu)

    


    

    
6985

    
    

    
    // The first menu in a hierarchy isn't so hovering doesn't get across (otherwise e.g. resizing borders with ImGuiButtonFlags_FlattenChildren would react), but top-most BeginMenu() will bypass that limitation.

    


    

    
6986

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindowFlags window_flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu | ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoNavFocus;

    


    

    
6987

    
    

    
    if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu)

    


    

    
6988

    
    

    
        window_flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow;

    


    

    
6989

    
    

    

    


    

    
6990

    
    

    
    // If a menu with same the ID was already submitted, we will append to it, matching the behavior of Begin().

    


    

    
6991

    
    

    
    // We are relying on a O(N) search - so O(N log N) over the frame - which seems like the most efficient for the expected small amount of BeginMenu() calls per frame.

    


    

    
6992

    
    

    
    // If somehow this is ever becoming a problem we can switch to use e.g. ImGuiStorage mapping key to last frame used.

    


    

    
6993

    
    

    
    if (g.MenusIdSubmittedThisFrame.contains(id))

    


    

    
6994

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
6995

    
    

    
        if (menu_is_open)

    


    

    
6996

    
    

    
            menu_is_open = BeginPopupEx(id, window_flags); // menu_is_open can be 'false' when the popup is completely clipped (e.g. zero size display)

    


    

    
6997

    
    

    
        else

    


    

    
6998

    
    

    
            g.NextWindowData.ClearFlags();          // we behave like Begin() and need to consume those values

    


    

    
6999

    
    

    
        return menu_is_open;

    


    

    
7000

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7001

    
    

    

    


    

    
7002

    
    

    
    // Tag menu as used. Next time BeginMenu() with same ID is called it will append to existing menu

    


    

    
7003

    
    

    
    g.MenusIdSubmittedThisFrame.push_back(id);

    


    

    
7004

    
    

    

    


    

    
7005

    
    

    
    ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);

    


    

    
7006

    
    

    

    


    

    
7007

    
    

    
    // Odd hack to allow hovering across menus of a same menu-set (otherwise we wouldn't be able to hover parent without always being a Child window)

    


    

    
7008

    
    

    
    // This is only done for items for the menu set and not the full parent window.

    


    

    
7009

    
    

    
    const bool menuset_is_open = IsRootOfOpenMenuSet();

    


    

    
7010

    
    

    
    if (menuset_is_open)

    


    

    
7011

    
    

    
        PushItemFlag(ImGuiItemFlags_NoWindowHoverableCheck, true);

    


    

    
7012

    
    

    

    


    

    
7013

    
    

    
    // The reference position stored in popup_pos will be used by Begin() to find a suitable position for the child menu,

    


    

    
7014

    
    

    
    // However the final position is going to be different! It is chosen by FindBestWindowPosForPopup().

    


    

    
7015

    
    

    
    // e.g. Menus tend to overlap each other horizontally to amplify relative Z-ordering.

    


    

    
7016

    
    

    
    ImVec2 popup_pos, pos = window->DC.CursorPos;

    


    

    
7017

    
    

    
    PushID(label);

    


    

    
7018

    
    

    
    if (!enabled)

    


    

    
7019

    
    

    
        BeginDisabled();

    


    

    
7020

    
    

    
    const ImGuiMenuColumns* offsets = &window->DC.MenuColumns;

    


    

    
7021

    
    

    
    bool pressed;

    


    

    
7022

    
    

    

    


    

    
7023

    
    

    
    // We use ImGuiSelectableFlags_NoSetKeyOwner to allow down on one menu item, move, up on another.

    


    

    
7024

    
    

    
    const ImGuiSelectableFlags selectable_flags = ImGuiSelectableFlags_NoHoldingActiveID | ImGuiSelectableFlags_NoSetKeyOwner | ImGuiSelectableFlags_SelectOnClick | ImGuiSelectableFlags_DontClosePopups;

    


    

    
7025

    
    

    
    if (window->DC.LayoutType == ImGuiLayoutType_Horizontal)

    


    

    
7026

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7027

    
    

    
        // Menu inside an horizontal menu bar

    


    

    
7028

    
    

    
        // Selectable extend their highlight by half ItemSpacing in each direction.

    


    

    
7029

    
    

    
        // For ChildMenu, the popup position will be overwritten by the call to FindBestWindowPosForPopup() in Begin()

    


    

    
7030

    
    

    
        popup_pos = ImVec2(pos.x - 1.0f - IM_FLOOR(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f), pos.y - style.FramePadding.y + window->MenuBarHeight());

    


    

    
7031

    
    

    
        window->DC.CursorPos.x += IM_FLOOR(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f);

    


    

    
7032

    
    

    
        PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_ItemSpacing, ImVec2(style.ItemSpacing.x * 2.0f, style.ItemSpacing.y));

    


    

    
7033

    
    

    
        float w = label_size.x;

    


    

    
7034

    
    

    
        ImVec2 text_pos(window->DC.CursorPos.x + offsets->OffsetLabel, window->DC.CursorPos.y + window->DC.CurrLineTextBaseOffset);

    


    

    
7035

    
    

    
        pressed = Selectable("", menu_is_open, selectable_flags, ImVec2(w, 0.0f));

    


    

    
7036

    
    

    
        RenderText(text_pos, label);

    


    

    
7037

    
    

    
        PopStyleVar();

    


    

    
7038

    
    

    
        window->DC.CursorPos.x += IM_FLOOR(style.ItemSpacing.x * (-1.0f + 0.5f)); // -1 spacing to compensate the spacing added when Selectable() did a SameLine(). It would also work to call SameLine() ourselves after the PopStyleVar().

    


    

    
7039

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7040

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7041

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7042

    
    

    
        // Menu inside a regular/vertical menu

    


    

    
7043

    
    

    
        // (In a typical menu window where all items are BeginMenu() or MenuItem() calls, extra_w will always be 0.0f.

    


    

    
7044

    
    

    
        //  Only when they are other items sticking out we're going to add spacing, yet only register minimum width into the layout system.

    


    

    
7045

    
    

    
        popup_pos = ImVec2(pos.x, pos.y - style.WindowPadding.y);

    


    

    
7046

    
    

    
        float icon_w = (icon && icon[0]) ? CalcTextSize(icon, NULL).x : 0.0f;

    


    

    
7047

    
    

    
        float checkmark_w = IM_FLOOR(g.FontSize * 1.20f);

    


    

    
7048

    
    

    
        float min_w = window->DC.MenuColumns.DeclColumns(icon_w, label_size.x, 0.0f, checkmark_w); // Feedback to next frame

    


    

    
7049

    
    

    
        float extra_w = ImMax(0.0f, GetContentRegionAvail().x - min_w);

    


    

    
7050

    
    

    
        ImVec2 text_pos(window->DC.CursorPos.x + offsets->OffsetLabel, window->DC.CursorPos.y + window->DC.CurrLineTextBaseOffset);

    


    

    
7051

    
    

    
        pressed = Selectable("", menu_is_open, selectable_flags | ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAvailWidth, ImVec2(min_w, 0.0f));

    


    

    
7052

    
    

    
        RenderText(text_pos, label);

    


    

    
7053

    
    

    
        if (icon_w > 0.0f)

    


    

    
7054

    
    

    
            RenderText(pos + ImVec2(offsets->OffsetIcon, 0.0f), icon);

    


    

    
7055

    
    

    
        RenderArrow(window->DrawList, pos + ImVec2(offsets->OffsetMark + extra_w + g.FontSize * 0.30f, 0.0f), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text), ImGuiDir_Right);

    


    

    
7056

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7057

    
    

    
    if (!enabled)

    


    

    
7058

    
    

    
        EndDisabled();

    


    

    
7059

    
    

    

    


    

    
7060

    
    

    
    const bool hovered = (g.HoveredId == id) && enabled && !g.NavDisableMouseHover;

    


    

    
7061

    
    

    
    if (menuset_is_open)

    


    

    
7062

    
    

    
        PopItemFlag();

    


    

    
7063

    
    

    

    


    

    
7064

    
    

    
    bool want_open = false;

    


    

    
7065

    
    

    
    bool want_close = false;

    


    

    
7066

    
    

    
    if (window->DC.LayoutType == ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical) // (window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu))

    


    

    
7067

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7068

    
    

    
        // Close menu when not hovering it anymore unless we are moving roughly in the direction of the menu

    


    

    
7069

    
    

    
        // Implement http://bjk5.com/post/44698559168/breaking-down-amazons-mega-dropdown to avoid using timers, so menus feels more reactive.

    


    

    
7070

    
    

    
        bool moving_toward_child_menu = false;

    


    

    
7071

    
    

    
        ImGuiPopupData* child_popup = (g.BeginPopupStack.Size < g.OpenPopupStack.Size) ? &g.OpenPopupStack[g.BeginPopupStack.Size] : NULL; // Popup candidate (testing below)

    


    

    
7072

    
    

    
        ImGuiWindow* child_menu_window = (child_popup && child_popup->Window && child_popup->Window->ParentWindow == window) ? child_popup->Window : NULL;

    


    

    
7073

    
    

    
        if (g.HoveredWindow == window && child_menu_window != NULL)

    


    

    
7074

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7075

    
    

    
            float ref_unit = g.FontSize; // FIXME-DPI

    


    

    
7076

    
    

    
            float child_dir = (window->Pos.x < child_menu_window->Pos.x) ? 1.0f : -1.0f;

    


    

    
7077

    
    

    
            ImRect next_window_rect = child_menu_window->Rect();

    


    

    
7078

    
    

    
            ImVec2 ta = (g.IO.MousePos - g.IO.MouseDelta);

    


    

    
7079

    
    

    
            ImVec2 tb = (child_dir > 0.0f) ? next_window_rect.GetTL() : next_window_rect.GetTR();

    


    

    
7080

    
    

    
            ImVec2 tc = (child_dir > 0.0f) ? next_window_rect.GetBL() : next_window_rect.GetBR();

    


    

    
7081

    
    

    
            float extra = ImClamp(ImFabs(ta.x - tb.x) * 0.30f, ref_unit * 0.5f, ref_unit * 2.5f);   // add a bit of extra slack.

    


    

    
7082

    
    

    
            ta.x += child_dir * -0.5f;

    


    

    
7083

    
    

    
            tb.x += child_dir * ref_unit;

    


    

    
7084

    
    

    
            tc.x += child_dir * ref_unit;

    


    

    
7085

    
    

    
            tb.y = ta.y + ImMax((tb.y - extra) - ta.y, -ref_unit * 8.0f);                           // triangle has maximum height to limit the slope and the bias toward large sub-menus

    


    

    
7086

    
    

    
            tc.y = ta.y + ImMin((tc.y + extra) - ta.y, +ref_unit * 8.0f);

    


    

    
7087

    
    

    
            moving_toward_child_menu = ImTriangleContainsPoint(ta, tb, tc, g.IO.MousePos);

    


    

    
7088

    
    

    
            //GetForegroundDrawList()->AddTriangleFilled(ta, tb, tc, moving_toward_child_menu ? IM_COL32(0,128,0,128) : IM_COL32(128,0,0,128)); // [DEBUG]

    


    

    
7089

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7090

    
    

    

    


    

    
7091

    
    

    
        // The 'HovereWindow == window' check creates an inconsistency (e.g. moving away from menu slowly tends to hit same window, whereas moving away fast does not)

    


    

    
7092

    
    

    
        // But we also need to not close the top-menu menu when moving over void. Perhaps we should extend the triangle check to a larger polygon.

    


    

    
7093

    
    

    
        // (Remember to test this on BeginPopup("A")->BeginMenu("B") sequence which behaves slightly differently as B isn't a Child of A and hovering isn't shared.)

    


    

    
7094

    
    

    
        if (menu_is_open && !hovered && g.HoveredWindow == window && !moving_toward_child_menu && !g.NavDisableMouseHover)

    


    

    
7095

    
    

    
            want_close = true;

    


    

    
7096

    
    

    

    


    

    
7097

    
    

    
        // Open

    


    

    
7098

    
    

    
        if (!menu_is_open && pressed) // Click/activate to open

    


    

    
7099

    
    

    
            want_open = true;

    


    

    
7100

    
    

    
        else if (!menu_is_open && hovered && !moving_toward_child_menu) // Hover to open

    


    

    
7101

    
    

    
            want_open = true;

    


    

    
7102

    
    

    
        if (g.NavId == id && g.NavMoveDir == ImGuiDir_Right) // Nav-Right to open

    


    

    
7103

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7104

    
    

    
            want_open = true;

    


    

    
7105

    
    

    
            NavMoveRequestCancel();

    


    

    
7106

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7107

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7108

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7109

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7110

    
    

    
        // Menu bar

    


    

    
7111

    
    

    
        if (menu_is_open && pressed && menuset_is_open) // Click an open menu again to close it

    


    

    
7112

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7113

    
    

    
            want_close = true;

    


    

    
7114

    
    

    
            want_open = menu_is_open = false;

    


    

    
7115

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7116

    
    

    
        else if (pressed || (hovered && menuset_is_open && !menu_is_open)) // First click to open, then hover to open others

    


    

    
7117

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7118

    
    

    
            want_open = true;

    


    

    
7119

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7120

    
    

    
        else if (g.NavId == id && g.NavMoveDir == ImGuiDir_Down) // Nav-Down to open

    


    

    
7121

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7122

    
    

    
            want_open = true;

    


    

    
7123

    
    

    
            NavMoveRequestCancel();

    


    

    
7124

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7125

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7126

    
    

    

    


    

    
7127

    
    

    
    if (!enabled) // explicitly close if an open menu becomes disabled, facilitate users code a lot in pattern such as 'if (BeginMenu("options", has_object)) { ..use object.. }'

    


    

    
7128

    
    

    
        want_close = true;

    


    

    
7129

    
    

    
    if (want_close && IsPopupOpen(id, ImGuiPopupFlags_None))

    


    

    
7130

    
    

    
        ClosePopupToLevel(g.BeginPopupStack.Size, true);

    


    

    
7131

    
    

    

    


    

    
7132

    
    

    
    IMGUI_TEST_ENGINE_ITEM_INFO(id, label, g.LastItemData.StatusFlags | ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Openable | (menu_is_open ? ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Opened : 0));

    


    

    
7133

    
    

    
    PopID();

    


    

    
7134

    
    

    

    


    

    
7135

    
    

    
    if (want_open && !menu_is_open && g.OpenPopupStack.Size > g.BeginPopupStack.Size)

    


    

    
7136

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7137

    
    

    
        // Don't reopen/recycle same menu level in the same frame, first close the other menu and yield for a frame.

    


    

    
7138

    
    

    
        OpenPopup(label);

    


    

    
7139

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7140

    
    

    
    else if (want_open)

    


    

    
7141

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7142

    
    

    
        menu_is_open = true;

    


    

    
7143

    
    

    
        OpenPopup(label);

    


    

    
7144

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7145

    
    

    

    


    

    
7146

    
    

    
    if (menu_is_open)

    


    

    
7147

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7148

    
    

    
        ImGuiLastItemData last_item_in_parent = g.LastItemData;

    


    

    
7149

    
    

    
        SetNextWindowPos(popup_pos, ImGuiCond_Always);                  // Note: misleading: the value will serve as reference for FindBestWindowPosForPopup(), not actual pos.

    


    

    
7150

    
    

    
        PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_ChildRounding, style.PopupRounding); // First level will use _PopupRounding, subsequent will use _ChildRounding

    


    

    
7151

    
    

    
        menu_is_open = BeginPopupEx(id, window_flags);                  // menu_is_open can be 'false' when the popup is completely clipped (e.g. zero size display)

    


    

    
7152

    
    

    
        PopStyleVar();

    


    

    
7153

    
    

    
        if (menu_is_open)

    


    

    
7154

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7155

    
    

    
            // Restore LastItemData so IsItemXXXX functions can work after BeginMenu()/EndMenu()

    


    

    
7156

    
    

    
            // (This fixes using IsItemClicked() and IsItemHovered(), but IsItemHovered() also relies on its support for ImGuiItemFlags_NoWindowHoverableCheck)

    


    

    
7157

    
    

    
            g.LastItemData = last_item_in_parent;

    


    

    
7158

    
    

    
            if (g.HoveredWindow == window)

    


    

    
7159

    
    

    
                g.LastItemData.StatusFlags |= ImGuiItemStatusFlags_HoveredWindow;

    


    

    
7160

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7161

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7162

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7163

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7164

    
    

    
        g.NextWindowData.ClearFlags(); // We behave like Begin() and need to consume those values

    


    

    
7165

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7166

    
    

    

    


    

    
7167

    
    

    
    return menu_is_open;

    


    

    
7168

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7169

    
    

    

    


    

    
7170

    
    

    
bool ImGui::BeginMenu(const char* label, bool enabled)

    


    

    
7171

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7172

    
    

    
    return BeginMenuEx(label, NULL, enabled);

    


    

    
7173

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7174

    
    

    

    


    

    
7175

    
    

    
void ImGui::EndMenu()

    


    

    
7176

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7177

    
    

    
    // Nav: When a left move request our menu failed, close ourselves.

    


    

    
7178

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7179

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
7180

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup);  // Mismatched BeginMenu()/EndMenu() calls

    


    

    
7181

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* parent_window = window->ParentWindow;  // Should always be != NULL is we passed assert.

    


    

    
7182

    
    

    
    if (window->BeginCount == window->BeginCountPreviousFrame)

    


    

    
7183

    
    

    
        if (g.NavMoveDir == ImGuiDir_Left && NavMoveRequestButNoResultYet())

    


    

    
7184

    
    

    
            if (g.NavWindow && (g.NavWindow->RootWindowForNav == window) && parent_window->DC.LayoutType == ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical)

    


    

    
7185

    
    

    
            {

    


    

    
7186

    
    

    
                ClosePopupToLevel(g.BeginPopupStack.Size - 1, true);

    


    

    
7187

    
    

    
                NavMoveRequestCancel();

    


    

    
7188

    
    

    
            }

    


    

    
7189

    
    

    

    


    

    
7190

    
    

    
    EndPopup();

    


    

    
7191

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7192

    
    

    

    


    

    
7193

    
    

    
bool ImGui::MenuItemEx(const char* label, const char* icon, const char* shortcut, bool selected, bool enabled)

    


    

    
7194

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7195

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();

    


    

    
7196

    
    

    
    if (window->SkipItems)

    


    

    
7197

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
7198

    
    

    

    


    

    
7199

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7200

    
    

    
    ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;

    


    

    
7201

    
    

    
    ImVec2 pos = window->DC.CursorPos;

    


    

    
7202

    
    

    
    ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);

    


    

    
7203

    
    

    

    


    

    
7204

    
    

    
    // See BeginMenuEx() for comments about this.

    


    

    
7205

    
    

    
    const bool menuset_is_open = IsRootOfOpenMenuSet();

    


    

    
7206

    
    

    
    if (menuset_is_open)

    


    

    
7207

    
    

    
        PushItemFlag(ImGuiItemFlags_NoWindowHoverableCheck, true);

    


    

    
7208

    
    

    

    


    

    
7209

    
    

    
    // We've been using the equivalent of ImGuiSelectableFlags_SetNavIdOnHover on all Selectable() since early Nav system days (commit 43ee5d73),

    


    

    
7210

    
    

    
    // but I am unsure whether this should be kept at all. For now moved it to be an opt-in feature used by menus only.

    


    

    
7211

    
    

    
    bool pressed;

    


    

    
7212

    
    

    
    PushID(label);

    


    

    
7213

    
    

    
    if (!enabled)

    


    

    
7214

    
    

    
        BeginDisabled();

    


    

    
7215

    
    

    

    


    

    
7216

    
    

    
    // We use ImGuiSelectableFlags_NoSetKeyOwner to allow down on one menu item, move, up on another.

    


    

    
7217

    
    

    
    const ImGuiSelectableFlags selectable_flags = ImGuiSelectableFlags_SelectOnRelease | ImGuiSelectableFlags_NoSetKeyOwner | ImGuiSelectableFlags_SetNavIdOnHover;

    


    

    
7218

    
    

    
    const ImGuiMenuColumns* offsets = &window->DC.MenuColumns;

    


    

    
7219

    
    

    
    if (window->DC.LayoutType == ImGuiLayoutType_Horizontal)

    


    

    
7220

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7221

    
    

    
        // Mimic the exact layout spacing of BeginMenu() to allow MenuItem() inside a menu bar, which is a little misleading but may be useful

    


    

    
7222

    
    

    
        // Note that in this situation: we don't render the shortcut, we render a highlight instead of the selected tick mark.

    


    

    
7223

    
    

    
        float w = label_size.x;

    


    

    
7224

    
    

    
        window->DC.CursorPos.x += IM_FLOOR(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f);

    


    

    
7225

    
    

    
        ImVec2 text_pos(window->DC.CursorPos.x + offsets->OffsetLabel, window->DC.CursorPos.y + window->DC.CurrLineTextBaseOffset);

    


    

    
7226

    
    

    
        PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_ItemSpacing, ImVec2(style.ItemSpacing.x * 2.0f, style.ItemSpacing.y));

    


    

    
7227

    
    

    
        pressed = Selectable("", selected, selectable_flags, ImVec2(w, 0.0f));

    


    

    
7228

    
    

    
        PopStyleVar();

    


    

    
7229

    
    

    
        if (g.LastItemData.StatusFlags & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Visible)

    


    

    
7230

    
    

    
            RenderText(text_pos, label);

    


    

    
7231

    
    

    
        window->DC.CursorPos.x += IM_FLOOR(style.ItemSpacing.x * (-1.0f + 0.5f)); // -1 spacing to compensate the spacing added when Selectable() did a SameLine(). It would also work to call SameLine() ourselves after the PopStyleVar().

    


    

    
7232

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7233

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7234

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7235

    
    

    
        // Menu item inside a vertical menu

    


    

    
7236

    
    

    
        // (In a typical menu window where all items are BeginMenu() or MenuItem() calls, extra_w will always be 0.0f.

    


    

    
7237

    
    

    
        //  Only when they are other items sticking out we're going to add spacing, yet only register minimum width into the layout system.

    


    

    
7238

    
    

    
        float icon_w = (icon && icon[0]) ? CalcTextSize(icon, NULL).x : 0.0f;

    


    

    
7239

    
    

    
        float shortcut_w = (shortcut && shortcut[0]) ? CalcTextSize(shortcut, NULL).x : 0.0f;

    


    

    
7240

    
    

    
        float checkmark_w = IM_FLOOR(g.FontSize * 1.20f);

    


    

    
7241

    
    

    
        float min_w = window->DC.MenuColumns.DeclColumns(icon_w, label_size.x, shortcut_w, checkmark_w); // Feedback for next frame

    


    

    
7242

    
    

    
        float stretch_w = ImMax(0.0f, GetContentRegionAvail().x - min_w);

    


    

    
7243

    
    

    
        pressed = Selectable("", false, selectable_flags | ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAvailWidth, ImVec2(min_w, 0.0f));

    


    

    
7244

    
    

    
        if (g.LastItemData.StatusFlags & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Visible)

    


    

    
7245

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7246

    
    

    
            RenderText(pos + ImVec2(offsets->OffsetLabel, 0.0f), label);

    


    

    
7247

    
    

    
            if (icon_w > 0.0f)

    


    

    
7248

    
    

    
                RenderText(pos + ImVec2(offsets->OffsetIcon, 0.0f), icon);

    


    

    
7249

    
    

    
            if (shortcut_w > 0.0f)

    


    

    
7250

    
    

    
            {

    


    

    
7251

}

static int IMGUI_CDECL TabItemComparerBySection(const void* lhs, const void* rhs)

{

    const ImGuiTabItem* a = (const ImGuiTabItem*)lhs;

    const ImGuiTabItem* b = (const ImGuiTabItem*)rhs;

    const int a_section = TabItemGetSectionIdx(a);

    const int b_section = TabItemGetSectionIdx(b);

    if (a_section != b_section)

        return a_section - b_section;

    return (int)(a->IndexDuringLayout - b->IndexDuringLayout);

    


    

    
7346

    
    

    
}

// The reason we're not calling it in BeginTabBar() is to leave a chance to the user to call the SetTabItemClosed() functions.

{

    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    {

        int curr_tab_section_n = TabItemGetSectionIdx(tab);

    


    

    
7519

    
    

    
        if (tab_dst_n > 0)

    


    

    
7520

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7521

    
    

    
            ImGuiTabItem* prev_tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[tab_dst_n - 1];

    


    

    
7522

    
    

    
            int prev_tab_section_n = TabItemGetSectionIdx(prev_tab);

    


    

    
7523

    
    

    
            if (curr_tab_section_n == 0 && prev_tab_section_n != 0)

    


    

    
7524

    
    

    
                need_sort_by_section = true;

    


    

    
7525

    
    

    
            if (prev_tab_section_n == 2 && curr_tab_section_n != 2)

    


    

    
7526

    
    

    
                need_sort_by_section = true;

    


    

    
7527

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7528

    
    

    

    


    

    
7529

    
    

    
        sections[curr_tab_section_n].TabCount++;

    


    

    
7530

    
    

    
        tab_dst_n++;

    


    

    
7531

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7532

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->Tabs.Size != tab_dst_n)

    


    

    
7533

    
    

    
        tab_bar->Tabs.resize(tab_dst_n);

    


    

    
7534

    
    

    

    


    

    
7535

    
    

    
    if (need_sort_by_section)

    


    

    
7536

    
    

    
        ImQsort(tab_bar->Tabs.Data, tab_bar->Tabs.Size, sizeof(ImGuiTabItem), TabItemComparerBySection);

    


    

    
7537

    
    

    

    


    

    
7538

    
    

    
    // Calculate spacing between sections

    


    

    
7539

    
    

    
    sections[0].Spacing = sections[0].TabCount > 0 && (sections[1].TabCount + sections[2].TabCount) > 0 ? g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x : 0.0f;

    


    

    
7540

    
    

    
    sections[1].Spacing = sections[1].TabCount > 0 && sections[2].TabCount > 0 ? g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x : 0.0f;

    


    

    
7541

    
    

    

    


    

    
7542

    
    

    
    // Setup next selected tab

    


    

    
7543

    
    

    
    ImGuiID scroll_to_tab_id = 0;

    


    

    
7544

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId)

    


    

    
7545

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7546

    
    

    
        tab_bar->SelectedTabId = tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId;

    


    

    
7547

    
    

    
        tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId = 0;

    


    

    
7548

    
    

    
        scroll_to_tab_id = tab_bar->SelectedTabId;

    


    

    
7549

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7550

    
    

    

    


    

    
7551

    
    

    
    // Process order change request (we could probably process it when requested but it's just saner to do it in a single spot).

    


    

    
7552

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId != 0)

    


    

    
7553

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7554

    
    

    
        if (TabBarProcessReorder(tab_bar))

    


    

    
7555

    
    

    
            if (tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId == tab_bar->SelectedTabId)

    


    

    
7556

    
    

    
                scroll_to_tab_id = tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId;

    


    

    
7557

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId = 0;

    


    

    
7558

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7559

    
    

    

    


    

    
7560

    
    

    
    // Tab List Popup (will alter tab_bar->BarRect and therefore the available width!)

    


    

    
7561

    
    

    
    const bool tab_list_popup_button = (tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_TabListPopupButton) != 0;

    


    

    
7562

    
    

    
    if (tab_list_popup_button)

    


    

    
7563

    
    

    
        if (ImGuiTabItem* tab_to_select = TabBarTabListPopupButton(tab_bar)) // NB: Will alter BarRect.Min.x!

    


    

    
7564

    
    

    
            scroll_to_tab_id = tab_bar->SelectedTabId = tab_to_select->ID;

    


    

    
7565

    
    

    

    


    

    
7566

    
    

    
    // Leading/Trailing tabs will be shrink only if central one aren't visible anymore, so layout the shrink data as: leading, trailing, central

    


    

    
7567

    
    

    
    // (whereas our tabs are stored as: leading, central, trailing)

    


    

    
7568

    
    

    
    int shrink_buffer_indexes[3] = { 0, sections[0].TabCount + sections[2].TabCount, sections[0].TabCount };

    


    

    
7569

    
    

    
    g.ShrinkWidthBuffer.resize(tab_bar->Tabs.Size);

    


    

    
7570

    
    

    

    


    

    
7571

    
    

    
    // Compute ideal tabs widths + store them into shrink buffer

    


    

    
7572

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* most_recently_selected_tab = NULL;

    


    

    
7573

    
    

    
    int curr_section_n = -1;

    


    

    
7574

    
    

    
    bool found_selected_tab_id = false;

    


    

    
7575

    
    

    
    for (int tab_n = 0; tab_n < tab_bar->Tabs.Size; tab_n++)

    


    

    
7576

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7577

    
    

    
        ImGuiTabItem* tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[tab_n];

    


    

    
7578

    
    

    
        IM_ASSERT(tab->LastFrameVisible >= tab_bar->PrevFrameVisible);

    


    

    
7579

    
    

    

    


    

    
7580

    
    

    
        if ((most_recently_selected_tab == NULL || most_recently_selected_tab->LastFrameSelected < tab->LastFrameSelected) && !(tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button))

    


    

    
7581

    
    

    
            most_recently_selected_tab = tab;

    


    

    
7582

    
    

    
        if (tab->ID == tab_bar->SelectedTabId)

    


    

    
7583

    
    

    
            found_selected_tab_id = true;

    


    

    
7584

    
    

    
        if (scroll_to_tab_id == 0 && g.NavJustMovedToId == tab->ID)

    


    

    
7585

    
    

    
            scroll_to_tab_id = tab->ID;

    


    

    
7586

    
    

    

    


    

    
7587

    
    

    
        // Refresh tab width immediately, otherwise changes of style e.g. style.FramePadding.x would noticeably lag in the tab bar.

    


    

    
7588

    
    

    
        // Additionally, when using TabBarAddTab() to manipulate tab bar order we occasionally insert new tabs that don't have a width yet,

    


    

    
7589

    
    

    
        // and we cannot wait for the next BeginTabItem() call. We cannot compute this width within TabBarAddTab() because font size depends on the active window.

    


    

    
7590

    
    

    
        const char* tab_name = tab_bar->GetTabName(tab);

    


    

    
7591

    
    

    
        const bool has_close_button_or_unsaved_marker = (tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoCloseButton) == 0 || (tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_UnsavedDocument);

    


    

    
7592

    
    

    
        tab->ContentWidth = (tab->RequestedWidth >= 0.0f) ? tab->RequestedWidth : TabItemCalcSize(tab_name, has_close_button_or_unsaved_marker).x;

    


    

    
7593

    
    

    

    


    

    
7594

    
    

    
        int section_n = TabItemGetSectionIdx(tab);

    


    

    
7595

    
    

    
        ImGuiTabBarSection* section = &sections[section_n];

    


    

    
7596

    
    

    
        section->Width += tab->ContentWidth + (section_n == curr_section_n ? g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x : 0.0f);

    


    

    
7597

    
    

    
        curr_section_n = section_n;

    


    

    
7598

    
    

    

    


    

    
7599

    
    

    
        // Store data so we can build an array sorted by width if we need to shrink tabs down

    


    

    
7600

    
    

    
        IM_MSVC_WARNING_SUPPRESS(6385);

    


    

    
7601

    
    

    
        ImGuiShrinkWidthItem* shrink_width_item = &g.ShrinkWidthBuffer[shrink_buffer_indexes[section_n]++];

    


    

    
7602

    
    

    
        shrink_width_item->Index = tab_n;

    


    

    
7603

    
    

    
        shrink_width_item->Width = shrink_width_item->InitialWidth = tab->ContentWidth;

    


    

    
7604

    
    

    
        tab->Width = ImMax(tab->ContentWidth, 1.0f);

    


    

    
7605

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7606

    
    

    

    


    

    
7607

    
    

    
    // Compute total ideal width (used for e.g. auto-resizing a window)

    


    

    
7608

    
    

    
    tab_bar->WidthAllTabsIdeal = 0.0f;

    


    

    
7609

    
    

    
    for (int section_n = 0; section_n < 3; section_n++)

    


    

    
7610

    
    

    
        tab_bar->WidthAllTabsIdeal += sections[section_n].Width + sections[section_n].Spacing;

    


    

    
7611

    
    

    

    


    

    
7612

    
    

    
    // Horizontal scrolling buttons

    


    

    
7613

    
    

    
    // (note that TabBarScrollButtons() will alter BarRect.Max.x)

    


    

    
7614

    
    

    
    if ((tab_bar->WidthAllTabsIdeal > tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth() && tab_bar->Tabs.Size > 1) && !(tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_NoTabListScrollingButtons) && (tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_FittingPolicyScroll))

    


    

    
7615

    
    

    
        if (ImGuiTabItem* scroll_and_select_tab = TabBarScrollingButtons(tab_bar))

    


    

    
7616

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7617

    
    

    
            scroll_to_tab_id = scroll_and_select_tab->ID;

    


    

    
7618

    
    

    
            if ((scroll_and_select_tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button) == 0)

    


    

    
7619

    
    

    
                tab_bar->SelectedTabId = scroll_to_tab_id;

    


    

    
7620

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7621

    
    

    

    


    

    
7622

    
    

    
    // Shrink widths if full tabs don't fit in their allocated space

    


    

    
7623

    
    

    
    float section_0_w = sections[0].Width + sections[0].Spacing;

    


    

    
7624

    
    

    
    float section_1_w = sections[1].Width + sections[1].Spacing;

    


    

    
7625

    
    

    
    float section_2_w = sections[2].Width + sections[2].Spacing;

    


    

    
7626

    
    

    
    bool central_section_is_visible = (section_0_w + section_2_w) < tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth();

    


    

    
7627

    
    

    
    float width_excess;

    


    

    
7628

    
    

    
    if (central_section_is_visible)

    


    

    
7629

    
    

    
        width_excess = ImMax(section_1_w - (tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth() - section_0_w - section_2_w), 0.0f); // Excess used to shrink central section

    


    

    
7630

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7631

    
    

    
        width_excess = (section_0_w + section_2_w) - tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth(); // Excess used to shrink leading/trailing section

    


    

    
7632

    
    

    

    


    

    
7633

    
    

    
    // With ImGuiTabBarFlags_FittingPolicyScroll policy, we will only shrink leading/trailing if the central section is not visible anymore

    


    

    
7634

    
    

    
    if (width_excess >= 1.0f && ((tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_FittingPolicyResizeDown) || !central_section_is_visible))

    


    

    
7635

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7636

    
    

    
        int shrink_data_count = (central_section_is_visible ? sections[1].TabCount : sections[0].TabCount + sections[2].TabCount);

    


    

    
7637

    
    

    
        int shrink_data_offset = (central_section_is_visible ? sections[0].TabCount + sections[2].TabCount : 0);

    


    

    
7638

    
    

    
        ShrinkWidths(g.ShrinkWidthBuffer.Data + shrink_data_offset, shrink_data_count, width_excess);

    


    

    
7639

    
    

    

    


    

    
7640

    
    

    
        // Apply shrunk values into tabs and sections

    


    

    
7641

    
    

    
        for (int tab_n = shrink_data_offset; tab_n < shrink_data_offset + shrink_data_count; tab_n++)

    


    

    
7642

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7643

    
    

    
            ImGuiTabItem* tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[g.ShrinkWidthBuffer[tab_n].Index];

    


    

    
7644

    
    

    
            float shrinked_width = IM_FLOOR(g.ShrinkWidthBuffer[tab_n].Width);

    


    

    
7645

    
    

    
            if (shrinked_width < 0.0f)

    


    

    
7646

    
    

    
                continue;

    


    

    
7647

    
    

    

    


    

    
7648

    
    

    
            shrinked_width = ImMax(1.0f, shrinked_width);

    


    

    
7649

    
    

    
            int section_n = TabItemGetSectionIdx(tab);

    


    

    
7650

    
    

    
            sections[section_n].Width -= (tab->Width - shrinked_width);

    


    

    
7651

    
    

    
            tab->Width = shrinked_width;

    


    

    
7652

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7653

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7654

    
    

    

    


    

    
7655

    
    

    
    // Layout all active tabs

    


    

    
7656

    
    

    
    int section_tab_index = 0;

    


    

    
7657

    
    

    
    float tab_offset = 0.0f;

    


    

    
7658

    
    

    
    tab_bar->WidthAllTabs = 0.0f;

    


    

    
7659

    
    

    
    for (int section_n = 0; section_n < 3; section_n++)

    


    

    
7660

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7661

    
    

    
        ImGuiTabBarSection* section = &sections[section_n];

    


    

    
7662

    
    

    
        if (section_n == 2)

    


    

    
7663

    
    

    
            tab_offset = ImMin(ImMax(0.0f, tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth() - section->Width), tab_offset);

    


    

    
7664

    
    

    

    


    

    
7665

    
    

    
        for (int tab_n = 0; tab_n < section->TabCount; tab_n++)

    


    

    
7666

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7667

    
    

    
            ImGuiTabItem* tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[section_tab_index + tab_n];

    


    

    
7668

    
    

    
            tab->Offset = tab_offset;

    


    

    
7669

    
    

    
            tab->NameOffset = -1;

    


    

    
7670

    
    

    
            tab_offset += tab->Width + (tab_n < section->TabCount - 1 ? g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x : 0.0f);

    


    

    
7671

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7672

    
    

    
        tab_bar->WidthAllTabs += ImMax(section->Width + section->Spacing, 0.0f);

    


    

    
7673

    
    

    
        tab_offset += section->Spacing;

    


    

    
7674

    
    

    
        section_tab_index += section->TabCount;

    


    

    
7675

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7676

    
    

    

    


    

    
7677

    
    

    
    // Clear name buffers

    


    

    
7678

    
    

    
    tab_bar->TabsNames.Buf.resize(0);

    


    

    
7679

    
    

    

    


    

    
7680

    
    

    
    // If we have lost the selected tab, select the next most recently active one

    


    

    
7681

    
    

    
    if (found_selected_tab_id == false)

    


    

    
7682

    
    

    
        tab_bar->SelectedTabId = 0;

    


    

    
7683

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->SelectedTabId == 0 && tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId == 0 && most_recently_selected_tab != NULL)

    


    

    
7684

    
    

    
        scroll_to_tab_id = tab_bar->SelectedTabId = most_recently_selected_tab->ID;

    


    

    
7685

    
    

    

    


    

    
7686

    
    

    
    // Lock in visible tab

    


    

    
7687

    
    

    
    tab_bar->VisibleTabId = tab_bar->SelectedTabId;

    


    

    
7688

    
    

    
    tab_bar->VisibleTabWasSubmitted = false;

    


    

    
7689

    
    

    

    


    

    
7690

    
    

    
    // CTRL+TAB can override visible tab temporarily

    


    

    
7691

    
    

    
    if (g.NavWindowingTarget != NULL && g.NavWindowingTarget->DockNode && g.NavWindowingTarget->DockNode->TabBar == tab_bar)

    


    

    
7692

    
    

    
        tab_bar->VisibleTabId = scroll_to_tab_id = g.NavWindowingTarget->TabId;

    


    

    
7693

    
    

    

    


    

    
7694

    
    

    
    // Update scrolling

    


    

    
7695

    
    

    
    if (scroll_to_tab_id != 0)

    


    

    
7696

    
    

    
        TabBarScrollToTab(tab_bar, scroll_to_tab_id, sections);

    


    

    
7697

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ScrollingAnim = TabBarScrollClamp(tab_bar, tab_bar->ScrollingAnim);

    


    

    
7698

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ScrollingTarget = TabBarScrollClamp(tab_bar, tab_bar->ScrollingTarget);

    


    

    
7699

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->ScrollingAnim != tab_bar->ScrollingTarget)

    


    

    
7700

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7701

    
    

    
        // Scrolling speed adjust itself so we can always reach our target in 1/3 seconds.

    


    

    
7702

    
    

    
        // Teleport if we are aiming far off the visible line

    


    

    
7703

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed = ImMax(tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed, 70.0f * g.FontSize);

    


    

    
7704

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed = ImMax(tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed, ImFabs(tab_bar->ScrollingTarget - tab_bar->ScrollingAnim) / 0.3f);

    


    

    
7705

    
    

    
        const bool teleport = (tab_bar->PrevFrameVisible + 1 < g.FrameCount) || (tab_bar->ScrollingTargetDistToVisibility > 10.0f * g.FontSize);

    


    

    
7706

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingAnim = teleport ? tab_bar->ScrollingTarget : ImLinearSweep(tab_bar->ScrollingAnim, tab_bar->ScrollingTarget, g.IO.DeltaTime * tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed);

    


    

    
7707

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7708

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7709

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7710

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingSpeed = 0.0f;

    


    

    
7711

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7712

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ScrollingRectMinX = tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x + sections[0].Width + sections[0].Spacing;

    


    

    
7713

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ScrollingRectMaxX = tab_bar->BarRect.Max.x - sections[2].Width - sections[1].Spacing;

    


    

    
7714

    
    

    

    


    

    
7715

    
    

    
    // Actual layout in host window (we don't do it in BeginTabBar() so as not to waste an extra frame)

    


    

    
7716

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
7717

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = tab_bar->BarRect.Min;

    


    

    
7718

    
    

    
    ItemSize(ImVec2(tab_bar->WidthAllTabs, tab_bar->BarRect.GetHeight()), tab_bar->FramePadding.y);

    


    

    
7719

    
    

    
    window->DC.IdealMaxPos.x = ImMax(window->DC.IdealMaxPos.x, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x + tab_bar->WidthAllTabsIdeal);

    


    

    
7720

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7721

    
    

    

    


    

    
7722

    
    

    
// Dockable uses Name/ID in the global namespace. Non-dockable items use the ID stack.

    


    

    
7723

    
    

    
static ImU32   ImGui::TabBarCalcTabID(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, const char* label, ImGuiWindow* docked_window)

    


    

    
7724

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7725

    
    

    
    if (docked_window != NULL)

    


    

    
7726

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7727

    
    

    
        IM_UNUSED(tab_bar);

    


    

    
7728

    
    

    
        IM_ASSERT(tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_DockNode);

    


    

    
7729

    
    

    
        ImGuiID id = docked_window->TabId;

    


    

    
7730

    
    

    
        KeepAliveID(id);

    


    

    
7731

    
    

    
        return id;

    


    

    
7732

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7733

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7734

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7735

    
    

    
        ImGuiWindow* window = GImGui->CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
7736

    
    

    
        return window->GetID(label);

    


    

    
7737

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7738

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7739

    
    

    

    


    

    
7740

    
    

    
static float ImGui::TabBarCalcMaxTabWidth()

    


    

    
7741

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7742

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7743

    
    

    
    return g.FontSize * 20.0f;

    


    

    
7744

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7745

    
    

    

    


    

    
7746

    
    

    
ImGuiTabItem* ImGui::TabBarFindTabByID(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, ImGuiID tab_id)

    


    

    
7747

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7748

    
    

    
    if (tab_id != 0)

    


    

    
7749

    
    

    
        for (int n = 0; n < tab_bar->Tabs.Size; n++)

    


    

    
7750

    
    

    
            if (tab_bar->Tabs[n].ID == tab_id)

    


    

    
7751

    
    

    
                return &tab_bar->Tabs[n];

    


    

    
7752

    
    

    
    return NULL;

    


    

    
7753

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7754

    
    

    

    


    

    
7755

    
    

    
// FIXME: See references to #2304 in TODO.txt

    


    

    
7756

    
    

    
ImGuiTabItem* ImGui::TabBarFindMostRecentlySelectedTabForActiveWindow(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar)

    


    

    
7757

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7758

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* most_recently_selected_tab = NULL;

    


    

    
7759

    
    

    
    for (int tab_n = 0; tab_n < tab_bar->Tabs.Size; tab_n++)

    


    

    
7760

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7761

    
    

    
        ImGuiTabItem* tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[tab_n];

    


    

    
7762

    
    

    
        if (most_recently_selected_tab == NULL || most_recently_selected_tab->LastFrameSelected < tab->LastFrameSelected)

    


    

    
7763

    
    

    
            if (tab->Window && tab->Window->WasActive)

    


    

    
7764

    
    

    
                most_recently_selected_tab = tab;

    


    

    
7765

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7766

    
    

    
    return most_recently_selected_tab;

    


    

    
7767

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7768

    
    

    

    


    

    
7769

    
    

    
// The purpose of this call is to register tab in advance so we can control their order at the time they appear.

    


    

    
7770

    
    

    
// Otherwise calling this is unnecessary as tabs are appending as needed by the BeginTabItem() function.

    


    

    
7771

    
    

    
void ImGui::TabBarAddTab(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, ImGuiTabItemFlags tab_flags, ImGuiWindow* window)

    


    

    
7772

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7773

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7774

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(TabBarFindTabByID(tab_bar, window->TabId) == NULL);

    


    

    
7775

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(g.CurrentTabBar != tab_bar);  // Can't work while the tab bar is active as our tab doesn't have an X offset yet, in theory we could/should test something like (tab_bar->CurrFrameVisible < g.FrameCount) but we'd need to solve why triggers the commented early-out assert in BeginTabBarEx() (probably dock node going from implicit to explicit in same frame)

    


    

    
7776

    
    

    

    


    

    
7777

    
    

    
    if (!window->HasCloseButton)

    


    

    
7778

    
    

    
        tab_flags |= ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoCloseButton;       // Set _NoCloseButton immediately because it will be used for first-frame width calculation.

    


    

    
7779

    
    

    

    


    

    
7780

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem new_tab;

    


    

    
7781

    
    

    
    new_tab.ID = window->TabId;

    


    

    
7782

    
    

    
    new_tab.Flags = tab_flags;

    


    

    
7783

    
    

    
    new_tab.LastFrameVisible = tab_bar->CurrFrameVisible;   // Required so BeginTabBar() doesn't ditch the tab

    


    

    
7784

    
    

    
    if (new_tab.LastFrameVisible == -1)

    


    

    
7785

    
    

    
        new_tab.LastFrameVisible = g.FrameCount - 1;

    


    

    
7786

    
    

    
    new_tab.Window = window;                                // Required so tab bar layout can compute the tab width before tab submission

    


    

    
7787

    
    

    
    tab_bar->Tabs.push_back(new_tab);

    


    

    
7788

    
    

    
}

// The *TabId fields be already set by the docking system _before_ the actual TabItem was created, so we clear them regardless.

    


    

    
7791

    
    

    
void ImGui::TabBarRemoveTab(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, ImGuiID tab_id)

    


    

    
7792

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7793

    
    

    
    if (ImGuiTabItem* tab = TabBarFindTabByID(tab_bar, tab_id))

    


    

    
7794

    
    

    
        tab_bar->Tabs.erase(tab);

    


    

    
7795

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->VisibleTabId == tab_id)      { tab_bar->VisibleTabId = 0; }

    


    

    
7796

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->SelectedTabId == tab_id)     { tab_bar->SelectedTabId = 0; }

    


    

    
7797

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId == tab_id) { tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId = 0; }

    


    

    
7798

    
    

    
}

// Called on manual closure attempt

    


    

    
7801

    
    

    
void ImGui::TabBarCloseTab(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, ImGuiTabItem* tab)

    


    

    
7802

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7803

    
    

    
    if (tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button)

    


    

    
7804

    
    

    
        return; // A button appended with TabItemButton().

    


    

    
7805

    
    

    

    


    

    
7806

    
    

    
    if (!(tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_UnsavedDocument))

    


    

    
7807

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7808

    
    

    
        // This will remove a frame of lag for selecting another tab on closure.

    


    

    
7809

    
    

    
        // However we don't run it in the case where the 'Unsaved' flag is set, so user gets a chance to fully undo the closure

    


    

    
7810

    
    

    
        tab->WantClose = true;

    


    

    
7811

    
    

    
        if (tab_bar->VisibleTabId == tab->ID)

    


    

    
7812

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7813

    
    

    
            tab->LastFrameVisible = -1;

    


    

    
7814

    
    

    
            tab_bar->SelectedTabId = tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId = 0;

    


    

    
7815

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7816

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7817

    
    

    
    else

    


    

    
7818

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7819

    
    

    
        // Actually select before expecting closure attempt (on an UnsavedDocument tab user is expect to e.g. show a popup)

    


    

    
7820

    
    

    
        if (tab_bar->VisibleTabId != tab->ID)

    


    

    
7821

    
    

    
            tab_bar->NextSelectedTabId = tab->ID;

    


    

    
7822

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7823

    
    

    
}

static float ImGui::TabBarScrollClamp(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, float scrolling)

    


    

    
7826

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7827

    
    

    
    scrolling = ImMin(scrolling, tab_bar->WidthAllTabs - tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth());

    


    

    
7828

    
    

    
    return ImMax(scrolling, 0.0f);

    


    

    
7829

    
    

    
}

// Note: we may scroll to tab that are not selected! e.g. using keyboard arrow keys

    


    

    
7832

    
    

    
static void ImGui::TabBarScrollToTab(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, ImGuiID tab_id, ImGuiTabBarSection* sections)

    


    

    
7833

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7834

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* tab = TabBarFindTabByID(tab_bar, tab_id);

    


    

    
7835

    
    

    
    if (tab == NULL)

    


    

    
7836

    
    

    
        return;

    


    

    
7837

    
    

    
    if (tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_)

    


    

    
7838

    
    

    
        return;

    


    

    
7839

    
    

    

    


    

    
7840

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7841

    
    

    
    float margin = g.FontSize * 1.0f; // When to scroll to make Tab N+1 visible always make a bit of N visible to suggest more scrolling area (since we don't have a scrollbar)

    


    

    
7842

    
    

    
    int order = tab_bar->GetTabOrder(tab);

    


    

    
7843

    
    

    

    


    

    
7844

    
    

    
    // Scrolling happens only in the central section (leading/trailing sections are not scrolling)

    


    

    
7845

    
    

    
    // FIXME: This is all confusing.

    


    

    
7846

    
    

    
    float scrollable_width = tab_bar->BarRect.GetWidth() - sections[0].Width - sections[2].Width - sections[1].Spacing;

    


    

    
7847

    
    

    

    


    

    
7848

    
    

    
    // We make all tabs positions all relative Sections[0].Width to make code simpler

    


    

    
7849

    
    

    
    float tab_x1 = tab->Offset - sections[0].Width + (order > sections[0].TabCount - 1 ? -margin : 0.0f);

    


    

    
7850

    
    

    
    float tab_x2 = tab->Offset - sections[0].Width + tab->Width + (order + 1 < tab_bar->Tabs.Size - sections[2].TabCount ? margin : 1.0f);

    


    

    
7851

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ScrollingTargetDistToVisibility = 0.0f;

    


    

    
7852

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->ScrollingTarget > tab_x1 || (tab_x2 - tab_x1 >= scrollable_width))

    


    

    
7853

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7854

    
    

    
        // Scroll to the left

    


    

    
7855

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingTargetDistToVisibility = ImMax(tab_bar->ScrollingAnim - tab_x2, 0.0f);

    


    

    
7856

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingTarget = tab_x1;

    


    

    
7857

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7858

    
    

    
    else if (tab_bar->ScrollingTarget < tab_x2 - scrollable_width)

    


    

    
7859

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7860

    
    

    
        // Scroll to the right

    


    

    
7861

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingTargetDistToVisibility = ImMax((tab_x1 - scrollable_width) - tab_bar->ScrollingAnim, 0.0f);

    


    

    
7862

    
    

    
        tab_bar->ScrollingTarget = tab_x2 - scrollable_width;

    


    

    
7863

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7864

    
    

    
}

void ImGui::TabBarQueueReorder(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, const ImGuiTabItem* tab, int offset)

    


    

    
7867

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7868

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(offset != 0);

    


    

    
7869

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId == 0);

    


    

    
7870

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId = tab->ID;

    


    

    
7871

    
    

    
    tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset = (ImS16)offset;

    


    

    
7872

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7873

    
    

    

    


    

    
7874

    
    

    
void ImGui::TabBarQueueReorderFromMousePos(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar, const ImGuiTabItem* src_tab, ImVec2 mouse_pos)

    


    

    
7875

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7876

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7877

    
    

    
    IM_ASSERT(tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId == 0);

    


    

    
7878

    
    

    
    if ((tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_Reorderable) == 0)

    


    

    
7879

    
    

    
        return;

    


    

    
7880

    
    

    

    


    

    
7881

    
    

    
    const bool is_central_section = (src_tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_) == 0;

    


    

    
7882

    
    

    
    const float bar_offset = tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x - (is_central_section ? tab_bar->ScrollingTarget : 0);

    


    

    
7883

    
    

    

    


    

    
7884

    
    

    
    // Count number of contiguous tabs we are crossing over

    


    

    
7885

    
    

    
    const int dir = (bar_offset + src_tab->Offset) > mouse_pos.x ? -1 : +1;

    


    

    
7886

    
    

    
    const int src_idx = tab_bar->Tabs.index_from_ptr(src_tab);

    


    

    
7887

    
    

    
    int dst_idx = src_idx;

    


    

    
7888

    
    

    
    for (int i = src_idx; i >= 0 && i < tab_bar->Tabs.Size; i += dir)

    


    

    
7889

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
7890

    
    

    
        // Reordered tabs must share the same section

    


    

    
7891

    
    

    
        const ImGuiTabItem* dst_tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[i];

    


    

    
7892

    
    

    
        if (dst_tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoReorder)

    


    

    
7893

    
    

    
            break;

    


    

    
7894

    
    

    
        if ((dst_tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_) != (src_tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_))

    


    

    
7895

    
    

    
            break;

    


    

    
7896

    
    

    
        dst_idx = i;

    


    

    
7897

    
    

    

    


    

    
7898

    
    

    
        // Include spacing after tab, so when mouse cursor is between tabs we would not continue checking further tabs that are not hovered.

    


    

    
7899

    
    

    
        const float x1 = bar_offset + dst_tab->Offset - g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x;

    


    

    
7900

    
    

    
        const float x2 = bar_offset + dst_tab->Offset + dst_tab->Width + g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x;

    


    

    
7901

    
    

    
        //GetForegroundDrawList()->AddRect(ImVec2(x1, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.y), ImVec2(x2, tab_bar->BarRect.Max.y), IM_COL32(255, 0, 0, 255));

    


    

    
7902

    
    

    
        if ((dir < 0 && mouse_pos.x > x1) || (dir > 0 && mouse_pos.x < x2))

    


    

    
7903

    
    

    
            break;

    


    

    
7904

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
7905

    
    

    

    


    

    
7906

    
    

    
    if (dst_idx != src_idx)

    


    

    
7907

    
    

    
        TabBarQueueReorder(tab_bar, src_tab, dst_idx - src_idx);

    


    

    
7908

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7909

    
    

    

    


    

    
7910

    
    

    
bool ImGui::TabBarProcessReorder(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar)

    


    

    
7911

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7912

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* tab1 = TabBarFindTabByID(tab_bar, tab_bar->ReorderRequestTabId);

    


    

    
7913

    
    

    
    if (tab1 == NULL || (tab1->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoReorder))

    


    

    
7914

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
7915

    
    

    

    


    

    
7916

    
    

    
    //IM_ASSERT(tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_Reorderable); // <- this may happen when using debug tools

    


    

    
7917

    
    

    
    int tab2_order = tab_bar->GetTabOrder(tab1) + tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset;

    


    

    
7918

    
    

    
    if (tab2_order < 0 || tab2_order >= tab_bar->Tabs.Size)

    


    

    
7919

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
7920

    
    

    

    


    

    
7921

    
    

    
    // Reordered tabs must share the same section

    


    

    
7922

    
    

    
    // (Note: TabBarQueueReorderFromMousePos() also has a similar test but since we allow direct calls to TabBarQueueReorder() we do it here too)

    


    

    
7923

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* tab2 = &tab_bar->Tabs[tab2_order];

    


    

    
7924

    
    

    
    if (tab2->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoReorder)

    


    

    
7925

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
7926

    
    

    
    if ((tab1->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_) != (tab2->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_))

    


    

    
7927

    
    

    
        return false;

    


    

    
7928

    
    

    

    


    

    
7929

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem item_tmp = *tab1;

    


    

    
7930

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* src_tab = (tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset > 0) ? tab1 + 1 : tab2;

    


    

    
7931

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* dst_tab = (tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset > 0) ? tab1 : tab2 + 1;

    


    

    
7932

    
    

    
    const int move_count = (tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset > 0) ? tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset : -tab_bar->ReorderRequestOffset;

    


    

    
7933

    
    

    
    memmove(dst_tab, src_tab, move_count * sizeof(ImGuiTabItem));

    


    

    
7934

    
    

    
    *tab2 = item_tmp;

    


    

    
7935

    
    

    

    


    

    
7936

    
    

    
    if (tab_bar->Flags & ImGuiTabBarFlags_SaveSettings)

    


    

    
7937

    
    

    
        MarkIniSettingsDirty();

    


    

    
7938

    
    

    
    return true;

    


    

    
7939

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
7940

    
    

    

    


    

    
7941

    
    

    
static ImGuiTabItem* ImGui::TabBarScrollingButtons(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar)

    


    

    
7942

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
7943

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
7944

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
7945

    
    

    

    


    

    
7946

    
    

    
    const ImVec2 arrow_button_size(g.FontSize - 2.0f, g.FontSize + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f);

    


    

    
7947

    
    

    
    const float scrolling_buttons_width = arrow_button_size.x * 2.0f;

    


    

    
7948

    
    

    

    


    

    
7949

    
    

    
    const ImVec2 backup_cursor_pos = window->DC.CursorPos;

    


    

    
7950

    
    

    
    //window->DrawList->AddRect(ImVec2(tab_bar->BarRect.Max.x - scrolling_buttons_width, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.y), ImVec2(tab_bar->BarRect.Max.x, tab_bar->BarRect.Max.y), IM_COL32(255,0,0,255));

    


    

    
7951

    
    

    

    


    

    
7952

    
    

    
    int select_dir = 0;

    


    

    
7953

    
    

    
    ImVec4 arrow_col = g.Style.Colors[ImGuiCol_Text];

    


    

    
7954

    
    

    
    arrow_col.w *= 0.5f;

    


    

    
7955

    
    

    

    


    

    
7956

    
    

    
    PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Text, arrow_col);

    


    

    
7957

    
    

    
    PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Button, ImVec4(0, 0, 0, 0));

    


    

    
7958

    
    

    
    const float backup_repeat_delay = g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay;

    


    

    
7959

    
    

    
    const float backup_repeat_rate = g.IO.KeyRepeatRate;

    


    

    
7960

    
    

    
    g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay = 0.250f;

    


    

    
7961

    
    

    
    g.IO.KeyRepeatRate = 0.200f;

    


    

    
7962

    
    

    
    float x = ImMax(tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x, tab_bar->BarRect.Max.x - scrolling_buttons_width);

    


    

    
7963

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2(x, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.y);

    


    

    
7964

    
    

    
    if (ArrowButtonEx("##<", ImGuiDir_Left, arrow_button_size, ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick | ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat))

    


    

    
7965

    
    

    
        select_dir = -1;

    


    

    
7966

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2(x + arrow_button_size.x, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.y);

    


    

    
7967

    
    

    
    if (ArrowButtonEx("##>", ImGuiDir_Right, arrow_button_size, ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick | ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat))

    


    

    
7968

    
    

    
        select_dir = +1;

    


    

    
7969

    
    

    
    PopStyleColor(2);

    


    

    
7970

    
    

    
    g.IO.KeyRepeatRate = backup_repeat_rate;

    


    

    
7971

    
    

    
    g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay = backup_repeat_delay;

    


    

    
7972

    
    

    

    


    

    
7973

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* tab_to_scroll_to = NULL;

    


    

    
7974

    
    

    
    if (select_dir != 0)

    


    

    
7975

    
    

    
        if (ImGuiTabItem* tab_item = TabBarFindTabByID(tab_bar, tab_bar->SelectedTabId))

    


    

    
7976

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
7977

    
    

    
            int selected_order = tab_bar->GetTabOrder(tab_item);

    


    

    
7978

    
    

    
            int target_order = selected_order + select_dir;

    


    

    
7979

    
    

    

    


    

    
7980

    
    

    
            // Skip tab item buttons until another tab item is found or end is reached

    


    

    
7981

    
    

    
            while (tab_to_scroll_to == NULL)

    


    

    
7982

    
    

    
            {

    


    

    
7983

    
    

    
                // If we are at the end of the list, still scroll to make our tab visible

    


    

    
7984

    
    

    
                tab_to_scroll_to = &tab_bar->Tabs[(target_order >= 0 && target_order < tab_bar->Tabs.Size) ? target_order : selected_order];

    


    

    
7985

    
    

    

    


    

    
7986

    
    

    
                // Cross through buttons

    


    

    
7987

    
    

    
                // (even if first/last item is a button, return it so we can update the scroll)

    


    

    
7988

    
    

    
                if (tab_to_scroll_to->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button)

    


    

    
7989

    
    

    
                {

    


    

    
7990

    
    

    
                    target_order += select_dir;

    


    

    
7991

    
    

    
                    selected_order += select_dir;

    


    

    
7992

    
    

    
                    tab_to_scroll_to = (target_order < 0 || target_order >= tab_bar->Tabs.Size) ? tab_to_scroll_to : NULL;

    


    

    
7993

    
    

    
                }

    


    

    
7994

    
    

    
            }

    


    

    
7995

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
7996

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = backup_cursor_pos;

    


    

    
7997

    
    

    
    tab_bar->BarRect.Max.x -= scrolling_buttons_width + 1.0f;

    


    

    
7998

    
    

    

    


    

    
7999

    
    

    
    return tab_to_scroll_to;

    


    

    
8000

    
    

    
}

    


    

    
8001

    
    

    

    


    

    
8002

    
    

    
static ImGuiTabItem* ImGui::TabBarTabListPopupButton(ImGuiTabBar* tab_bar)

    


    

    
8003

    
    

    
{

    


    

    
8004

    
    

    
    ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;

    


    

    
8005

    
    

    
    ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;

    


    

    
8006

    
    

    

    


    

    
8007

    
    

    
    // We use g.Style.FramePadding.y to match the square ArrowButton size

    


    

    
8008

    
    

    
    const float tab_list_popup_button_width = g.FontSize + g.Style.FramePadding.y;

    


    

    
8009

    
    

    
    const ImVec2 backup_cursor_pos = window->DC.CursorPos;

    


    

    
8010

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2(tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x - g.Style.FramePadding.y, tab_bar->BarRect.Min.y);

    


    

    
8011

    
    

    
    tab_bar->BarRect.Min.x += tab_list_popup_button_width;

    


    

    
8012

    
    

    

    


    

    
8013

    
    

    
    ImVec4 arrow_col = g.Style.Colors[ImGuiCol_Text];

    


    

    
8014

    
    

    
    arrow_col.w *= 0.5f;

    


    

    
8015

    
    

    
    PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Text, arrow_col);

    


    

    
8016

    
    

    
    PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Button, ImVec4(0, 0, 0, 0));

    


    

    
8017

    
    

    
    bool open = BeginCombo("##v", NULL, ImGuiComboFlags_NoPreview | ImGuiComboFlags_HeightLargest);

    


    

    
8018

    
    

    
    PopStyleColor(2);

    


    

    
8019

    
    

    

    


    

    
8020

    
    

    
    ImGuiTabItem* tab_to_select = NULL;

    


    

    
8021

    
    

    
    if (open)

    


    

    
8022

    
    

    
    {

    


    

    
8023

    
    

    
        for (int tab_n = 0; tab_n < tab_bar->Tabs.Size; tab_n++)

    


    

    
8024

    
    

    
        {

    


    

    
8025

    
    

    
            ImGuiTabItem* tab = &tab_bar->Tabs[tab_n];

    


    

    
8026

    
    

    
            if (tab->Flags & ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button)

    


    

    
8027

    
    

    
                continue;

    


    

    
8028

    
    

    

    


    

    
8029

    
    

    
            const char* tab_name = tab_bar->GetTabName(tab);

    


    

    
8030

    
    

    
            if (Selectable(tab_name, tab_bar->SelectedTabId == tab->ID))

    


    

    
8031

    
    

    
                tab_to_select = tab;

    


    

    
8032

    
    

    
        }

    


    

    
8033

    
    

    
        EndCombo();

    


    

    
8034

    
    

    
    }

    


    

    
8035

    
    

    

    


    

    
8036

    
    

    
    window->DC.CursorPos = backup_cursor_pos;

    


    

    
8037

    
    

    
    return tab_to_select;

    


    

    
8038

    
    

    
}
